  "title": "Personal Assistant/Operations Manager | Central| Mon–Fri 9-6 | Up to $5,000",
  "description": "<p><strong>Operations Manager/Personal Assistant | Central| Mon–Fri 9-6 | Up to $5,000</strong><br /></p><p>Location: Central</p><p>Working Hours: Monday to Friday, 9:00 AM – 6:00PM</p><p>Salary Range: Up to SGD$5,000</p><p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We are seeking an experienced Operations Manager to lead\nand oversee operational controls, administrative functions, and internal processes. This role plays a key part in strengthening organizational efficiency, supporting management, and ensuring smooth day-to-day operations\nacross office, warehouse, and service administration functions.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and oversee daily operations, administrative processes, and internal controls</li><li>Develop operational plans, budgets, and performance tracking to improve efficiency</li><li>Coordinate with landlords, vendors, contractors, and service providers on operational matters</li><li>Manage warehouse, inventory, and import/export logistics to ensure accuracy and cost efficiency</li><li>Liaise with IT vendors to support system maintenance and software updates</li><li>Oversee facilities repairs and maintenance within approved budgets</li><li>Support manpower planning and implement strategies to meet staffing needs</li><li>Lead and manage Office Administration and Service Administration teams</li><li>Manage calendars, meetings, travel arrangements, and schedules for the General Manager</li><li>Communicate and liaise with internal teams and external stakeholders</li><li>Perform ad-hoc duties as assigned by the General Manager</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Business Administration, Operations, or related fields</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience</li><li>Strong written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Independent, responsible, and resourceful with strong problem-solving abilities</li><li>IT-savvy with good proficiency in Microsoft Office</li><li>Customer-service oriented mindset</li><li>Basic accounting knowledge is an advantage</li><li>Piano playing ability or interest in music appreciation is an added advantage</li></ul><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li>Monday–Friday office hours</li><li>Exposure to senior management and cross-functional operations</li><li>Opportunity to take ownership of operations in a professional environment</li></ul><p><strong>Apply Now</strong></p><p>If you are a proactive operations professional looking for a leadership-focused role, send your resume in MS Word format to:\n<strong>Vanessa.chua@crew.sg</strong></p><p>Please include your <strong>availability, notice period, and expected salary</strong>.</p><p><em>* Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em></p><p>Vanessa Chua Peng Teng (R25158315)</p><p>HRnet Ventures Pte Ltd - CREW by HRnet</p><p>E.A. 24C2435</p>",
